```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"details": {
"resource_requirements": {
"partition": "DGXq",
"node": "node19",
"modules": ["cuda11.2/toolkit/11.2.0"],
"environment_variables": {
"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES": "6"
},
"python_script": "main_frame.py"
},
"script_parameters": {
"train": {
"num_class": 51,
"data_dir": "/export/home/xxx/xxx/datasets/HMDB51/jpegs_256",
"train_list": "/export/home/xxx/xxx/work/dataset_config/HMDB51/lists/trainlist01.txt",
"val_list": "/export/home/xxx/xxx/work/dataset_config/HMDB51/lists/trainlist01.txt",
"arch": "resnet50",
"pretrain": True,
"batch_size": 256,
"lr": 0.04,
"wd": 1e-5,
"epochs": 50,
"lr_step": [20, 40],
"model_name": "hmdb51-split01-resnet50-pretrain"
},
"test": {
"num_class": 51,
"data_dir": "/export/home/xxx/xxx/datasets/HMDB51/jpegs_256",
"test_list": "/export/home/xxx/xxx/work/dataset_config/HMDB51/lists/trainlist01.txt",
"save_test_results": True,
"batch_size": 1024,
"model_name": "hmdb51-split01-resnet50-pretrain"
}
}
}
```

This script uses SLURM to manage the execution of the python script "main_frame.py". It uses the DGXq partition and the node "node19". It requires the CUDA toolkit version 11.2.0 and sets the environment variable CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES to 6. The script runs the "main_frame.py" twice, once for training and once for testing with different parameters.
